description:
&lt;p&gt;We are offering the opportunity to work as part of a dynamic service delivering Intermediate Care services to the population of Bournemouth. The role of Community Rehabilitation Assistant involves working with frail and older people in the community, supporting them to attain maximum independence through outcome based rehabilitation, helping to reduce the risk of admission to hospital or long term care, and supporting patients being discharged from hospital for assessment at home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of a multi-disciplinary team you would have the opportunity to work with skilled professionals, including Occupational Therapists, Physiotherapists, Nurses and Advanced Practitioners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are excellent opportunities for learning and development, in a role which is varied and exciting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full/Part time available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires a Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Joy Ainley&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Intermediate Care Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
